column5: BOQ is a weekender.Man thats alongggggggggg day Rob.  Nice fish.  Thanks for sharing.
Noice fishes!
Real beauty of a walleye  Quinte rocks for ice fishing. Hang on as the sunsets there is a good chance of a big walleye.  Tipping a jigging rap w/ minnow head works well.
The scuttlebutt back at the cars that day was that most of the groups did well in the am but not in the pm. I got mine at about 4:20pm and the 2 others at about 4:40pm.
~~~Great post bud thanks for sharing I'll be down there this weekend with posse, hope we do as well as you, or at least I hope I do as well
Finally looked at the gps today. The second spot was a 4km round trip. In the dark, after a long day, it felt like a lot more than 2 klics.
Nice fisheeees KK.  Worth every minute of that long day no doubt.  Love the action you described on the Rap...jig...pause.....JIG....BAM! cool.

Up a 3am. On the road with my brother by 4am. Meet our buddy at 7am. Holes drilled and lines in the water by 7:30am.  Nice fresh morning:   Moved around the first spot, only marked a few fish, and my brother was the only one to hook-up before lunch:   Headed in to a small town dinner in Desironto ($45 that the town of Innisfil will never see, plus 2 tanks of gas and gatoraid $140) and stoked the furnace for the afternoon.  Lunch for 3 guys, and I'm the smallest one by at least 80lbs: onion rings, burger and fries, poutine, toasted western omelette with extra toast and sausage, 2 bowls of potato soup and fish and chips.  Head out to our buddies second spot, and we're fishing by 2pm.  Set up a special tip-up at afternoon location.   Although set lines produced no fish for us.  Mark a lot more fish but can't get them to commit until I switch to a jigging rap after 4pm. First fish that shows after switching I stop jiggin', pause and then give it a quiver and BAM. Nice solid fish.      20 minutes later I got 2 more walleye around 2lbs and that was it except for some perch.  Long drive back to Barrie in a snow storm. in bed by midnight.
you have got to love a 21 hour day all in the name of fishing  nice to see you got some walleye
Wow, long day & cold too!  Nice lookin' eye there!  Going in the frying pan or swimming another day?
What a beauty.  Nice job.
Great report, fish and pics Rob I thought I had recognized that set line Great to see that you are putting it to good use Very nice walleye on the last pic Thanks for sharing Jacques
Thats a lonnnggg day glad you caught something nice for your trouble.   Art
I've heard those types of mornings called many things Rob, but fresh is a new one.  Glad to see you had a decent day out.

Thanks for sharing, I gots to get down there for a 2 day'er. Man after my own heart, putting in a good day of fishin. Some guys just fish for a couple hours and go home to watch Judge Judy or the Maple Leafs play Perseverance, pays off
Wow, that sure was a long day out there, but worth it for that beauty Rob!
Nice report Rob. I don't know which I enjoyed most. The Walleye pics or the lunch menu.
Well done Rob, perseverence pays off!
Big day, big fish, big lunch....who needs sleep?

The "big" one went right back down the hole that's way I didn't get a messure or a weight, although I should have at least eye balled it against the rod which is 32 inches.  The 2 smaller fish and a couple of perch were eaten today for lunch. My wife and our 2 year old son may like fresh fish even more than me.    They'll get some more use soon.    Me, that's who.
Awesome Dude Rob, just an observation, next time make sure you have the spool pointing down ward.... meaning the top should be flipped   Just like in the next pic
Great outing Rob!! Out with the brother.. how could you go wrong.
Great job, stuck with it an dit paid off.
Nice report man!  I've always wanted to try the one day trip from barrie to quinte.  After reading this report, I think I'll make it a weekend event!  Thanks for sharing!
Nice catch there.  Thanks for the post, MTBF

good report!! I did a day trip to quinte once...now i make a weekeend trip... body gets killed  anyone every catch on still lines at quinte... in the 4 trips ive made over the past 2 years my group has never got anything unless we were jiggin..
Solid eye Rob.  Good chilly days effort.
Sounds like a nice outing Rob I would love to see the pictures but all I get recently is these stupid red XXXXXXX`s on some pictures not all!

I have a buddy whose inlaws have a cottage right above the ferry outside of Picton. Next trip, I'm going to check for avaliblity   Now you tell me.    I'll bring a slide show for our fly-in in September.
Nice Trip, Want some feathers still? R
